y":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Describe the problem\n\nCurrently, Remote Functions can do Client Side Boundary Streaming with Snippets:\n```svelte\n<script lang=\"ts\">\n  import { browser } from '$app/environment'\n</script>\n\n{#snippet pending()}\n  <p class=\"skeleton\">loading...</p>\n{/snippet}\n\n<svelte:boundary pending={browser ? pending : undefined}>\n  <p>cars today: {await getCarsCount()}</p>\n</svelte:boundary>\n```\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/15719#issuecomment-4360094521\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/discussions/13897#discussioncomment-16775452\n\nAND there is a beta primative `query.live` (https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/15563) which replaced `query.stream` (https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/14292) for Readable Streams and Real Time (Live) Data.\n\nHowever, there needs to be a way to do SSR Streaming (with Promises) just like [Page Loaders](https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/load#Streaming-with-promises) can do.\n\n@Rich-Harris has said this is on the [TODO list](https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/discussions/13897#discussioncomment-16781318), but I didn't see an official Feature Request for it for us to follow.\n\nJ\n\n### Describe the proposed solution\n\nMaybe `query.ssr` or something.\n\n### Alternatives considered\n\nFor now, the only way to do this is to use a [loader function](https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/load#Streaming-with-promises).\n\nOR, you can load from the client (see above).\n\n\n### Importance\n\nnice to have\n\n### Additional Information\n\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/discussions/4831\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/12304\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/14086\n\nThis is also to CLARIFY for people like me that didn't understand the naming difference.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/15789/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sveltejs/kit/issues/15789/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29/events","html_url":"https://github.com/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29","id":4371918048,"node_id":"I_kwDOQLtV4M8AAAABBJYs4A","number":29,"title":"Declare \"svelte\" field in package.json so SvelteKit auto-bundles for SSR","user":{"login":"stickerdaniel","id":63877413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYzODc3NDEz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/63877413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel","html_url":"https://github.com/stickerdaniel","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/stickerdaniel/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-03T13:25:23Z","updated_at":"2026-05-06T06:26:07Z","closed_at":"2026-05-06T06:26:07Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"The published package does not declare a top-level `\"svelte\"` field in `package.json`. SvelteKit auto-adds dependencies with this field to `ssr.noExternal` (sveltejs/kit#1148, sveltejs/kit#904), which is required for Svelte component libraries that use runes or `svelte/internal/server` context APIs.\n\nWithout the field, SvelteKit externalizes the package during SSR. The package's compiled `setupAutumn` calls `useConvexClient` from `convex-svelte`, which calls `getContext` from a runtime-resolved svelte instance separate from the consumer's bundled svelte. With the next `convex-svelte` major (or any consumer using `@mmailaender/convex-svelte` directly), the dual-instance hazard surfaces as `lifecycle_outside_component` during prerender.\n\nSurfaced while bumping the better-auth ecosystem in `saas-starter` (stickerdaniel/saas-starter#343) — manual `ssr.noExternal` was added in vite.config.ts as a workaround.\n\n## Proposed fix\n\nAdd to `package.json`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"svelte\": \"./dist/svelte/index.js\"\n}\n```\n\nPath should match the primary Svelte entry. The `svelte` field is read directly by SvelteKit (separate from `exports`).\n\n## References\n\n- SvelteKit auto-bundling for Svelte component libraries: https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/1148\n- Auto-detection via `svelte` field: https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/904\n- Vite SSR options (`ssr.noExternal`): https://vite.dev/config/ssr-options.html#ssr-noexternal\n- SvelteKit packaging docs: https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/packaging","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/stickerdaniel/convex-autumn-svelte/issues/29/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://