},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-04-27T13:11:50Z","updated_at":"2026-04-27T13:12:14Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T13:12:14Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Beschreibung\n\n**Paket:** `@sveltejs/kit`\n**CVE:** [CVE-2026-40073](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-40073)\n**Advisory:** [GHSA-2crg-3p73-43xp](https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-2crg-3p73-43xp)\n**Schweregrad:** High (CVSS 8.2)\n**Betroffene Komponente:** Frontend (Svelte/Node.js)\n\n### Schwachstelle\n\n`@sveltejs/adapter-node` hat einen BODY_SIZE_LIMIT Bypass. Unter bestimmten Umständen können Requests die `BODY_SIZE_LIMIT`-Beschränkung auf SvelteKit-Anwendungen umgehen, die mit `adapter-node` laufen. Dies betrifft keine Body-Size-Limits auf anderen Ebenen des Application Stacks (WAF, Gateway, Plattform).\n\n**Betroffene Version:** <= 2.57.0\n**Gepatchte Version:** >= 2.57.1\n\n### Lösungsvorschlag\n\nUpdate `@sveltejs/kit` von `2.49.1` auf `>= 2.58.0`:\n\n```bash\ncd src/frontend\nnpm audit fix\n```\n\n### Build-Test Ergebnis\n\n`npm audit fix` aktualisiert `@sveltejs/kit` auf `2.58.0`. Frontend-Build (`vite build`) und Backend-Build (`dotnet build`) waren nach dem Update **erfolgreich**. Die Schwachstelle ist nach dem Update behoben.\n\n### Referenzen\n- https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-2crg-3p73-43xp\n- https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/releases/tag/@sveltejs/kit@2.57.1","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/eBizCon/risk-management-platform/issues/87/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/eBizCon/risk-management-platform/issues/87/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vitest-dev/vitest/issues/10319","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vitest-dev/vitest","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vitest-dev/vitest/issues/10319/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vitest-dev/vitest/issues/10319/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vitest-dev/vitest/issues/10319/events","html_url":"https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/issues/10319","id":4418248822,"node_id":"I_kwDOGekgx88AAAABB1kgdg","number":10319,"title":"browser: `dynamicImportPlugin` leaks into SSR environment, breaks SvelteKit dev middleware","user":{"login":"playday3008","id":18056374,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4MDU2Mzc0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/18056374?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008","html_url":"https://github.com/playday3008","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/playday3008/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":6032046747,"node_id":"LA_kwDOGekgx88AAAABZ4m6mw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vitest-dev/vitest/labels/p3-minor-bug","name":"p3-minor-bug","color":"BF4D31","default":false,"description":"An edge case that only affects very specific usage (priority)"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-11T05:17:00Z","updated_at":"2026-05-17T22:50:16Z","closed_at":"2026-05-17T22:50:16Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":{"id":16164983,"node_id":"IT_kwDOBbT8I84A9qh3","name":"Bug","description":"An unexpected problem or behavior","color":"red","created_at":"2024-02-11T21:10:56Z","updated_at":"2024-07-26T14:17:50Z","is_enabled":true},"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Describe the bug\n\n`dynamicImportPlugin` from `@vitest/mocker` wraps `import()` calls with `globalThis[\"__vitest_browser_runner__\"].wrapDynamicImport(...)`. The problem is it does this in every Vite environment, including `ssr`. That global only exists in the browser context, so any SSR-loaded module with a dynamic import blows up:\n\n```\nTypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'wrapDynamicImport')\n    at get_hooks (.svelte-kit/generated/server/internal.js:37:77)\n    at Server.init (node_modules/@sveltejs/kit/src/runtime/server/index.js:109:35)\n    at node_modules/@sveltejs/kit/src/exports/vite/dev/index.js:526:18\n```\n\nTests still pass, but stderr gets spammed with the TypeError on every request hitting SvelteKit's middleware.\n\n### What's actually happening\n\nI patched `transformRequest` on each Vite dev server environment to see where the plugin runs. Vite 8 creates three environments: `client`, `ssr`, `__vitest__`. The plugin transforms all three. Here's what ends up in the `ssr` environment:\n\n| Module | What it becomes |\n|---|---|\n| `.svelte-kit/generated/server/internal.js` | `await globalThis[\"__vitest_browser_runner__\"].wrapDynamicImport(() => __vite_ssr_dynamic_import__(\"/src/hooks.server.ts\"))` |\n| `@sveltejs/kit/src/runtime/server/utils.js` | `await globalThis[\"__vitest_browser_runner__\"].wrapDynamicImport(() => __vite_ssr_dynamic_import__('node:path'))` |\n| `@sveltejs/kit/src/runtime/telemetry/otel.js` | `globalThis[\"__vitest_browser_runner__\"].wrapDynamicImport(() => __vite_ssr_dynamic_import__(\"@opentelemetry/api\"))` |\n| `svelte/src/internal/server/render-context.js` | `globalThis[\"__vitest_browser_runner__\"].wrapDynamicImport(() => __vite_ssr_dynamic_import__('node:async_hooks'))` |\n| `svelte/src/internal/server/crypto.js` | `globalThis[\"__vitest_browser_runner__\"].wrapDynamicImport(() => __vite_ssr_dynamic_import__(module_name))` |\n\nNone of these should be transformed — they run server-side and the browser runner global doesn't exist there.\n\n### Workaround\n\nShim the global at the top of `vite.config.ts` before any imports:\n\n```ts\nglobalThis[\"__vitest_browser_runner__\"] ??= { wrapDynamicImport: (f: Function) => f() };\n```\n\nThis matches what the browser context sets — a passthrough. `??=` avoids overwriting the real runner.\n\n### Related\n\n- Same bug for web workers: #8960\n- This was originally filed against SvelteKit (wrong repo): https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/14149\n\n### Reproduction\n\nhttps://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/14149#issuecomment-4372199567\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\n    OS: Linux 6.19 Fedora Linux 44 (KDE Plasma Desktop Edition)\n    CPU: (16) x64 AMD Ryzen 9 7940HS w/ Radeon 780M Graphics\n    Memory: 38.82 GB / 86.22 GB\n    Container: Yes\n    Shell: 5.9 - /usr/bin/zsh\n  Binaries:\n    Node: 22.22.0 - /usr/bin/node\n    Yarn: 1.22.22 - /usr/bin/yarn\n    npm: 10.9.4 - /usr/bin/npm\n    pnpm: 10.33.0 - /usr/bin/pnpm\n    bun: 1.3.3 - /home/playday/.bun/bin/bun\n    Deno: 3.0.0 - /home/playday/.deno/bin/deno\n  Browsers:\n    Firefox: 150.0\n    Firefox Developer Edition: 150.0\n  npmPackages:\n    @vitest/browser: ^4.1.5 => 4.1.5 \n    @vitest/browser-playwright: ^4.1.5 => 4.1.5 \n    vite: ^8.0.0 => 8.0.10 \n    vitest: ^4.1.5 => 4.1.5 \n    vitest-browser-svelte: ^2.1.1 => 2.1.1\n```\n\n### Used Package Manager\n\nbun\n\n### Validations\n\n- [x] Follow our [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md)\n- [x] Read the [Contributing Guidelines](https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n- [x] Read the [docs](https://vitest.dev/guide/).\n- [x] Check that there isn't [already an issue](https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/issues) that reports the same bug to avoid creating a duplicate.\n- [x] Check that this is a concrete bug. For Q&A open a [GitHub Discussion](https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/discussions) or join our [Discord Chat Server](https://chat.vitest.dev).\n- [x] The provided reproduction is a [minimal reproducible example](https://stackoverflow.com/help/minimal-reproducible-example) of the bug.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vitest-dev/vitest/issues/10319/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vitest-dev/vitest/issues/10319/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/235","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/235/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/235/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/235/events","html_url":"https://github.com/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/235","id":4412981342,"node_id":"I_kwDOSYBYgc8AAAABBwjAXg","number":235,"title":"Add SvelteKit sample app to VERIFY-2 corpus (sveltejs/kit sites/kit.svelte.dev)","user":{"login":"cajasmota","id":5105329,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUxMDUzMjk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5105329?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/cajasmota"