by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Follow-up to #25 with the actual root cause and a concrete fix. The package does not declare a top-level `\"svelte\"` field in `package.json`. SvelteKit auto-adds dependencies that declare this field to `ssr.noExternal`, which keeps Svelte runes and `svelte/internal/server` context APIs running against the same bundled svelte instance as the consumer's compiled `.svelte` output (sveltejs/kit#1148, sveltejs/kit#904).\n\nWithout the field, SvelteKit treats the package as external during SSR. Its `import { setContext } from 'svelte'` resolves to a separate svelte module instance from the route chunks. The two have independent module-scoped `ssr_context` variables, so `setContext` throws `lifecycle_outside_component` even though the call happens inside a `$$renderer.component()` callback.\n\nReproducible since 0.6 via `createSvelteAuthClient` -> `resolveConvexClient` -> `setupConvex` -> `setConvexClientContext` -> `setContext` on every prerendered route in any consumer app. Confirmed by instrumenting `node_modules/svelte/src/internal/server/context.js`: `ssr_context` is `null` at the failing call even though the layout's compiled chunk has set it on its own bundled copy.\n\n## Proposed fix\n\nAdd to `package.json`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"svelte\": \"./dist/svelte/index.js\"\n}\n```\n\nPath should match the package's primary Svelte entry. The `svelte` field is read directly by SvelteKit (separate from `exports`) to identify Svelte component libraries.\n\n## Consumer workaround until released\n\n```ts\n// vite.config.ts\nssr: {\n  noExternal: ['@mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte']\n}\n```\n\n## References\n\n- SvelteKit auto-bundling for Svelte component libraries: https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/pull/1148\n- Auto-detection via `svelte` field: https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/issues/904\n- Vite SSR options (`ssr.noExternal`): https://vite.dev/config/ssr-options.html#ssr-noexternal\n- SvelteKit packaging docs: https://svelte.dev/docs/kit/packaging","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte/issues/28/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mmailaender/convex-better-auth-svelte/issues/28/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numerique-gouv/ami-notifications-api/issues/877","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numerique-gouv/ami-notifications-api","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numerique-gouv/ami-notifications-api/issues/877/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numerique-gouv/ami-notifications-api/issues/877/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/numerique-gouv/ami-notifications-api/issues/877/events","html_url":"https://github.com/numerique-gouv/ami-notifications-api/issues/877","id":4468649927,"node_id":"I_kwDOOSMCFs8AAAABClovxw","number":877,"title":"Ne pas utiliser de `target=...` dans le code svelte","user":{"login":"magopian","id":167767,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2Nzc2Nw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/167767?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian","html_url":"https://github.com/magopian","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/magopian/received_e