i.github.com/users/binsarjr/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/binsarjr/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":0,"closed_issues":42,"state":"open","created_at":"2026-04-28T21:18:53Z","updated_at":"2026-04-30T05:12:58Z","due_on":"2026-07-14T00:00:00Z","closed_at":null},"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-04-28T22:45:50Z","updated_at":"2026-04-28T23:59:54Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T23:59:54Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nDefine the monorepo workspace layout for `binsarjr/sveltego` aligned with `sveltejs/kit` while adapted to Go modules and `go.work`. This RFC sets the directory structure, module boundaries, and import paths for every package shipped from this repo.\n\n## Background\n\n`sveltejs/kit` ships ~10 packages from one repo via pnpm workspaces: `packages/kit` (core), `packages/adapter-*` (auto, cloudflare, netlify, node, static, vercel), `packages/enhanced-img`, `packages/amp`, `packages/package`, plus `playgrounds/basic`, `documentation/docs`, `test-utils`, `scripts`. Independent versions per package (`@sveltejs/kit@2.x`, `@sveltejs/adapter-cloudflare@4.x`).\n\nGo has equivalent capability via `go.work` and per-subdir `go.mod`. Tag format `packages/<name>/v<semver>` is the Go monorepo idiom (used by `googleapis/google-cloud-go`, `kubernetes/kubernetes` subprojects).\n\n## Goals\n\n- Mirror SvelteKit's mental model so contributors familiar with upstream find their bearings instantly.\n- Every package versioned and released independently.\n- Adapter-specific dependencies isolated from core (cloudflare workers SDK never pulled by core users).\n- Build-time, request-time, and public API code physically separated inside core.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- Splitting into multiple repos. Monorepo from day 1.\n- Bringing in pnpm or Node-based tooling for the Go side. Vite/pnpm only inside `packages/sveltego/runtime/client` and inside `documentation/`.\n- Lockstep versioning across packages.\n\n## Detailed Design\n\n### Root layout\n\n```\nsveltego/\n├── go.work  go.work.sum\n├── README.md  CLAUDE.md  AGENTS.md  CONTRIBUTING.md  STABILITY.md  LICENSE\n├── .github/  .githooks/  .editorconfig  .golangci.yml\n├── tasks/                              # plan + lessons (sveltego-specific)\n│\n├── packages/\n│   ├── sveltego/                       # core, = packages/kit upstream\n│   │   ├── go.mod                      # module github.com/binsarjr/sveltego\n│   │   ├── README.md  CHANGELOG.md  STABILITY.md\n│   │   ├── cmd/sveltego/               # CLI entry\n│   │   ├── core/                       # build-time\n│   │   │   ├── parser/  codegen/  manifest/  adapt/  config/  sync/  postbuild/\n│   │   ├── runtime/                    # request-time\n│   │   │   ├── server/  client/  components/\n│   │   │   ├── app/{navigation,state,forms}/\n│   │   │   └── env/\n│   │   ├── exports/                    # public API surface\n│   │   │   ├── kit/  hooks/  node/  vite/\n│   │   └── internal/\n│   │\n│   ├── adapter-auto/                   # module github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/adapter-auto\n│   ├── adapter-cloudflare/\n│   ├── adapter-docker/\n│   ├── adapter-lambda/\n│   ├── adapter-server/                 # ~ adapter-node\n│   ├── adapter-static/\n│   ├── enhanced-img/                   # standalone image opt\n│   ├── create-sveltego/                # scaffold + templates\n│   │   └── templates/{minimal,blog,dashboard}/\n│   ├── mcp/                            # MCP server (#71)\n│   └── lsp/                            # LSP for .svelte (#69)\n│\n├── playgrounds/\n│   └── basic/                          # in-tree smoke (#23)\n│\n├── documentation/\n│   └── docs/                           # markdown source (#62)\n│\n├── benchmarks/                         # (#60, #61)\n├── test-utils/                         # shared Go test helpers\n└── scripts/                            # release, sync, codegen helpers\n```\n\n### Module paths\n\nEach `packages/<name>/go.mod` declares:\n\n```\nmodule github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/<name>     // for adapter-*, enhanced-img, create-sveltego, mcp, lsp\nmodule github.com/binsarjr/sveltego             // for packages/sveltego (core)\n```\n\nThe `packages/` directory is a layout convention; it does not appear in import paths. Tag format: `packages/<name>/v<semver>` (e.g. `packages/adapter-cloudflare/v0.1.0`).\n\n### `go.work`\n\n```\ngo 1.22\n\nuse (\n    ./packages/sveltego\n    ./packages/adapter-auto\n    ./packages/adapter-cloudflare\n    ./packages/adapter-docker\n    ./packages/adapter-lambda\n    ./packages/adapter-server\n    ./packages/adapter-static\n    ./packages/enhanced-img\n    ./packages/create-sveltego\n    ./packages/mcp\n    ./packages/lsp\n    ./playgrounds/basic\n    ./benchmarks\n    ./test-utils\n)\n```\n\n### Examples policy\n\n`playgrounds/basic` is the only in-tree app. Larger examples (blog, dashboard, realworld-style) live in a separate repo `binsarjr/sveltego-examples` once `v1.0` ships. Issues #64, #65 will move there.\n\n### Dropped from upstream\n\n- `packages/amp` — AMP is deprecated tech, skipped.\n- `packages/package` — Go has native module publishing; `svelte-package` equivalent unnecessary.\n- `.changeset/` — replaced by `release-please` manifest mode (see #100).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `go.work` boots: `go build ./...` succeeds across all packages once skeleton lands.\n- [ ] Each package has its own `go.mod`, `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `STABILITY.md`.\n- [ ] Import paths follow the rules above and verified with `go mod tidy` in each module.\n- [ ] CI builds each package in isolation (no cross-pollination).\n- [ ] Tag `packages/sveltego/v0.0.0-bootstrap` resolvable with `go get github.com/binsarjr/sveltego@v0.0.0-bootstrap`.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- Smoke: `go build ./...` and `go vet ./...` from root.\n- Tag verification: create a throwaway tag, run `go get` from a temp module pointing at it, confirm Go resolves the correct subdir.\n- Per-package `go test ./...` runs without depending on sibling packages except via published interfaces.\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- The actual code inside each package (handled by other issues).\n- Examples beyond `playgrounds/basic` (see #64, #65 once they migrate).\n- Documentation site theme (#62).\n\n## Risks & Open Questions\n\n- **Multi-module tagging quirks.** Go's monorepo tagging is well-supported but contributors may be unfamiliar. Mitigation: document in `CONTRIBUTING.md` and automate via `release-please` (#100).\n- **`replace` directives in `go.work`** can mask version drift in CI vs released form. Mitigation: CI runs `go.work` disabled (`GOWORK=off`) on a matrix leg to verify each module installs cleanly from tags.\n- **Path collisions** if a package later wants to be split out. Mitigation: keep import path stable (`github.com/binsarjr/sveltego/<name>`), so a future split renames the repo, not the import.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Blocks: #5 (Go module bootstrap), #6 (CLI skeleton), every code-bearing issue.\n- Blocked by: none.\n\n## References\n\n- `sveltejs/kit` packages layout: https://github.com/sveltejs/kit/tree/main/packages\n- Go monorepo tagging: https://go.dev/ref/mod#vcs-version\n- Workspace mode: https://go.dev/ref/mod#workspaces\n- googleapis/google-cloud-go: https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-go (canonical Go monorepo example)\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/binsarjr/sveltego/issues/95/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,